         <abstract>
            <p>Let $p_k(x) = x^k + \cdots, k \in \mathbf{N}_0$, be the polynomials orthogonal on $\lbrack-1, +1\rbrack$ with respect to the positive measure $d\sigma$. We give sufficient conditions on the real numbers $\mu_j, j = 0,\ldots, m$, such that the linear combination of orthogonal polynomials $\sum^m_{j = 0}\mu_jp_{n - j}$ has $n$ simple zeros in (-1, +1) and that the interpolatory quadrature formula whose nodes are the zeros of $\sum^m_{j = 0}\mu_jp_{n - j}$ has positive weights.</p>
          </abstract>
